I think creating such a wrapper cannot be handled out of the box by Jackson only based on annotations, so a custom `Deserializer` is required.

```java
private static final TypeReference&lt;List&lt;Element&gt;&gt; ELEMENT_LIST_TYPEREF =
        new TypeReference&lt;&gt;() {};

@Override
public Group deserialize(JsonParser parser, DeserializationContext ctx) throws IOException {
    // Elements class is fully managed by the deserializer here
    // that&#39;s why there are no annotations in places where it occurs in the code
    var elements = new Elements();
    var elementNodes = parser.readValueAsTree()
                             .get(&quot;element&quot;);
    try (var traverse = elementNodes.traverse(parser.getCodec())) {
        List&lt;Element&gt; elementsList = traverse.readValueAs(ELEMENT_LIST_TYPEREF);
        elements.setElements(elementsList);
    }
    var group = new Group();
    group.setElements(elements);
    return group;
}
```

Module with deserializer can be registered like so:
```java
var module = new SimpleModule(&quot;GroupDeseriaizerModule&quot;);
module.addDeserializer(Group.class, new GroupDeserializer());
xmlMapper.registerModule(module);
```

We&#39;re registering a deserializer for `Group` as `Elements` class is an artificial wrapper and it&#39;s not marked with Jackson annotations. If we did mark it, it could be harder to parse the elements and save it for the object (each `element` from the XML is a separate deserialized instance).

---

[Here you can find a repository][1] where I&#39;ve reproduced the problem and applied the deserializer code shown above. [The test][2] passed before the changes and now it also passes (I had to add an additional extraction `.extracting(Group::getElements)` since a new wrapper&#39;s been added).


  [1]: https://github.com/Jonarzz/stack-overflow/tree/73340254/spring-boot-module/src/main/java/io/github/jonarzz
  [2]: https://github.com/Jonarzz/stack-overflow/blob/73340254/spring-boot-module/src/test/java/io/github/jonarzz/XmlMapperTest.java#L27

