answers.body_markdown:
        g.drawImage(image, 0, 0, 810, 1440, null);
        super.paintComponent(g);

Your code is drawing an image and then invoking `super.paintComonent()` which paints the background of the panel over top of the image.

The proper order should be:

        super.paintComponent(g);
        g.drawImage (image, 0, 0, 810, 1440, null);

Why are you hardcoding 810, 1440? My screen resolution is 1024 x 768?

If you are trying to fill the entire area of the panel then you should be using the `getWidth()` and `getHeight()` methods.

    paintComponent(this.getGraphics());
    this.image = image;

Never invoke the paintComponent(...) method directly. Swing will invoke that method when the components needs to be repainted. 

Instead you just invoke the `repaint()` method.

How do you expect to paint the new image if you don&#39;t change the image variable until AFTER you try to paint the component?

